The paper deals with the complexity of path enumeration in weighted temporal graphs, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The introduction of bicriteria temporal min-cost path problems suggests a focus on optimization and decision-making (cs.AI). The use of efficient algorithms and polynomial time delay and space requirements suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The consideration of pareto-optimal solutions and finding efficient paths suggests a focus on information theory and signal processing (cs.IT). Finally, the use of temporal graphs and the consideration of early arrival times suggests a focus on social and information networks (cs.SI).
